---
import ProseLayout from '../layouts/ProseLayout.astro';
import ControllerIdentity from '../components/privacy/ControllerIdentity.astro';
import ChildrensPrivacy from '../components/privacy/ChildrensPrivacy.astro';
import PrivacyContact from '../components/privacy/PrivacyContact.astro';
---

<ProseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How GLANCE Apps handles your data. Short version: we don't collect it."
  lastUpdated="July 10, 2026"
>
  <p class="lead">
    Short version: GLANCE Apps does not collect, store, or share your personal
    data. Your information stays on your device.
  </p>

  <ControllerIdentity>
    <p>
      This privacy policy covers our publisher-level practices and the
      glance-apps.com website. Each app may have additional privacy details
      specific to its features; see the privacy policy linked from each app's
      product page.
    </p>
  </ControllerIdentity>

  <h2>Data stored on your device</h2>
  <p>
    All content you create within our Apps is stored locally on your device
    using your platform's standard on-device storage. This data remains under
    your control at all times.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use your platform's automatic backup service (iCloud Backup, Google
    Backup, or similar), your device data may be backed up as part of your
    standard device backup. This is governed by your platform provider's privacy
    policy.
  </p>

  <h2>Optional cloud sync</h2>
  <p>
    Some Apps offer optional cloud sync to a destination you control, such as
    WebDAV, Nextcloud, a self-hosted GLANCEvault instance, or iCloud Drive.
    GLANCE Apps does not operate any of these sync servers.
  </p>
  <p>
    When you sync to a GLANCEvault instance you host, your data is always
    encrypted client-side before leaving your device; the server stores encrypted
    content and never has access to your item contents or your passphrase. When
    you sync to WebDAV or Nextcloud, client-side encryption is optional and off by
    default; enable each app's sync-encryption option to encrypt your data before
    upload. When you sync to iCloud Drive, your data is stored in your personal
    iCloud account under Apple's standard encryption, governed by Apple's privacy
    policy. See each app's privacy policy for the details of its encryption model.
  </p>
  <p>
    Sync is off by default.
  </p>

  <h2>Data we do not collect</h2>
  <p>
    Our Apps are designed to operate entirely on your device. We do not:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Require you to create an account</li>
    <li>Collect personally identifiable information</li>
    <li>Store your notes, entries, or any app content on any servers we control (the web versions of some Apps route sync traffic through a stateless relay we host, in transit only and never stored; see each app's privacy policy)</li>
    <li>Track your location</li>
    <li>Use advertising identifiers</li>
    <li>Sell or share your data with third parties</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We do not use third-party analytics services. Your platform's distribution
    service (such as Apple's App Store Connect or Google Play Console) may share
    aggregated, anonymized crash and usage data with us if you have opted into
    analytics on your device. This data cannot be used to identify you individually.
  </p>

  <h2>This website</h2>
  <p>
    The glance-apps.com website is a static site served via Vercel. Vercel may
    collect standard web server logs (IP address, request times, page URLs) for
    operational purposes. We do not use cookies, tracking pixels, or analytics
    scripts on this site.
  </p>

  <ChildrensPrivacy />

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    If we make material changes to this policy, we will update the "Last updated"
    date at the top of this page and notify users through the Apps or this website
    before changes take effect.
  </p>

  <PrivacyContact />
</ProseLayout>
